.TH DETACH 1 "2021-07-04" "detach-process" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
detach \- spawn a new process and detach it from the current session
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B detach
.RI program " [ARGS...]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B detach
utility launches a program in a separate session so it continues running
independently of the interactive shell.
It forks, starts a new session, redirects standard input to
.IR /dev/null ,
and redirects standard output and standard error to temporary files in
.IR /tmp .
The parent process displays the child PID and the paths of the temporary
files, then terminates.
.SH OUTPUT
On success, the parent process outputs:
.TP
.B PID:
The process ID of the detached child process.
.TP
.B stdout:
The file used to capture the child's standard output.
.TP
.B stderr:
The file used to capture the child's standard error output.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B > 0
An error was encountered.
.SH EXAMPLES
Start a ping command detached from the current session:
.PP
.RS
detach ping -c 10 google.com
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /tmp/stdout.XXXXXX
A temporary file for standard output generated by
.BR mkstemp (3).
.TP
.I /tmp/stderr.XXXXXX
A temporary file for standard error generated by
.BR mkstemp (3).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mkstemp (3),
.BR setsid (2),
.BR fork (2),
.BR execvp (3)
